    <p>{`Docusaurus supports the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax"
      }}>{`Markdown`}</a>{` syntax and has some additional features.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "front-matter"
    }}>{`Front Matter`}</h2>
    <p>{`Markdown documents can have associated metadata at the top called `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://jekyllrb.com/docs/front-matter/"
      }}>{`Front Matter`}</a>{`:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-md"
      }}>{`---
id: my-doc
title: My document title
description: My document description
sidebar_label: My doc
---

Markdown content
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "markdown-links"
    }}>{`Markdown links`}</h2>
    <p>{`Regular Markdown links are supported using url paths or relative file paths.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-md"
      }}>{`Let's see how to [Create a page](/create-a-page).
`}</code></pre>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-md"
      }}>{`Let's see how to [Create a page](./create-a-page.md).
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Let's see how to `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/create-a-page"
      }}>{`Create a page`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "markdown-images"
    }}>{`Markdown images`}</h2>
    <p>{`Regular Markdown images are supported.`}</p>
    <p>{`Add an image at `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`static/img/docusaurus.png`}</inlineCode>{` and use this Markdown declaration:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-md"
      }}>{`![Docusaurus logo](/img/docusaurus.png)
`}</code></pre>
    <p><img alt={"Docusaurus logo"} src={require("!url-loader?limit=10000&name=assets/images/[name]-[hash].[ext]&fallback=file-loader!/Users/sebastienlorber/Desktop/projects/docusaurus/packages/docusaurus-init/templates/classic/static/img/docusaurus.png").default} /></p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "code-blocks"
    }}>{`Code Blocks`}</h2>
    <p>{`Markdown code blocks are supported with Syntax highlighting.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`\`\`\`jsx title="src/components/HelloDocusaurus.js"
function HelloDocusaurus() {
    return (
        <h1>Hello, Docusaurus!</h1>
    )
}
\`\`\`
`}</code></pre>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-jsx",
        "metastring": "title=\"src/components/HelloDocusaurus.js\"",
        "title": "\"src/components/HelloDocusaurus.js\""
      }}>{`function HelloDocusaurus() {
  return <h1>Hello, Docusaurus!</h1>;
}
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "admonitions"
    }}>{`Admonitions`}</h2>
    <p>{`Docusaurus has a special syntax to create admonitions and callouts:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`:::tip My tip

Use this awesome feature option

:::

:::danger Take care

This action is dangerous

:::
`}</code></pre>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-tip alert alert--success"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
